Write a program that outputs the top n elements from a list.

Example:

k = 2; list = [7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1]
==> [6, 7]

// We need to get the two greatest elements and then sort those elements 
// We can solve this by sorting the list, getting the first two elements, and sorting those two elements.

fn largest(n: usize, xs: &[i32]) -> Vec<i32> {

    let mut nums: Vec<i32> = xs.to_vec();
    nums.sort_by(|a, b| b.cmp(a));
    nums.truncate(n);
    nums.sort();
    nums 
}
